Whenever I install AVC and Chatterer, this log happens:

Executing: MiniAVC - 1.0.2.4

Assembly: /home/(name)/.steam/steam/SteamApps/common/Kerbal Space Program/GameData/GameData/Chatterer/Plugins/MiniAVC.dll

[Log 15:43:08.8641510]: KSP-AVC was detected... Unloading MiniAVC!

[Log 15:43:10.3071690]: Starter was destroyed.

Hi,

Harmless message here.

I bundled MiniAVC with Chatterer, but as you are using the full AVC mod it disable MiniAVC and it use the full one instead.

So, how does that change anything? It still crashes and stuff.

The log that you have post, is it full ? And can you explain a little more what is your crash, please you also can read this : How To Get Support
Okay, I think I got the wrong log. I'll find the correct log.

Okay, here's the log.

http://tny.cz/ba8eb387

It seems to be me running out of memory. Any things to decrease this? (like compressing textures or something)

Hello, why you don't use the KSP 64 bits on Linux? this can easily correct your memory problem.

If you don't know how to do this you can read this: Linux KSP on Steam

And if you search something to decrease memory, you can look this: Active Texture Management but that's useless on Linux KSP 64 bits

Oh this is it, out of memory issue !

I didn't see this one coming, when I saw Linux I thought you were using 64bits version already ^^

As Malah said, 64bits version should fix your issue.
